00:09.092 --> 00:11.512
making small incisions

00:09.092 --> 00:11.512
into the wall of the eye

00:11.553 --> 00:13.054
to allow the introduction

00:11.553 --> 00:13.054
of instruments

00:13.096 --> 00:15.056
(drill whirring)

00:13.096 --> 00:15.056
into the vitreous cavity.

00:15.098 --> 00:16.433
Is there

00:15.098 --> 00:16.433
anything else on?

00:16.475 --> 00:17.935
Dad, this is

00:16.475 --> 00:17.935
interesting.

00:17.977 --> 00:19.353
I might be a

00:17.977 --> 00:19.353
doctor someday.

00:19.394 --> 00:20.896
You're right,

00:19.394 --> 00:20.896
you're right.

00:20.938 --> 00:23.231
The draining of the vitreous,

00:20.938 --> 00:23.231
the clear, gel-like fluid

00:23.273 --> 00:25.066
that fills

00:23.273 --> 00:25.066
the back of the eye...

00:25.108 --> 00:27.945
Ah! Uh, I'm going

00:25.108 --> 00:27.945
to go read.

