01:00.561 --> 01:02.396
of me now ♪

01:02.437 --> 01:05.941
♪ And you're not so big ♪

01:05.983 --> 01:10.612
♪ Life is unfair. ♪

01:10.654 --> 01:11.906
Come on!

01:11.947 --> 01:13.114
You boys are late.

01:13.156 --> 01:14.616
I want you out of this house

01:13.156 --> 01:14.616
in 30 seconds.

01:14.658 --> 01:15.951
Let's show some hustle.

01:15.993 --> 01:17.411
We've got time.

01:17.452 --> 01:20.205
When we're really late, our

01:17.452 --> 01:20.205
lunches are on the front lawn.

01:24.167 --> 01:26.127
Mom, Reese...

01:26.169 --> 01:27.838
Go, go, go, go!

01:26.169 --> 01:27.838
(grunts)

01:27.880 --> 01:30.131
Okay, I'm doing dry

01:27.880 --> 01:30.131
cleaner, mechanic

01:30.173 --> 01:31.132
and post office.

01:31.174 --> 01:32.593
You're doing groceries and DMV,

01:31.174 --> 01:32.593
right?

01:32.634 --> 01:33.761
Right.

01:32.634 --> 01:33.761
You got the cable bill?

01:33.802 --> 01:35.429
Great. Bye, guy.

01:41.184 --> 01:43.645
Did I just say

01:41.184 --> 01:43.645
"Bye, guy" to you?

01:43.687 --> 01:45.022
I'm pretty sure you did.

01:45.064 --> 01:46.815
"Guy?" I-I-I called you "guy"?!

01:46.857 --> 01:48.067
How can that happen?

01:48.108 --> 01:49.651
I've never done that before.

01:49.693 --> 01:51.612
Hal, it's a lapse; it

01:49.693 --> 01:51.612
doesn't mean anything.

01:51.653 --> 01:53.321
"Guy"?!

01:51.653 --> 01:53.321
Hal, it happens.

01:53.363 --> 01:55.156
Let's get one thing clear.

01:55.198 --> 01:59.160
In no way, shape, or form

01:55.198 --> 01:59.160
do I think of you as a guy.

01:59.202 --> 02:00.203
You are a gorgeous,

02:00.245 --> 02:02.163
exciting, feminine goddess

02:02.205 --> 02:06.167
that I still don't know

02:02.205 --> 02:06.167
what I've done to deserve.

02:06.209 --> 02:07.878
Do you understand that?

02:07.920 --> 02:09.838
Yes.

02:13.216 --> 02:15.052
Let's do this walking.

02:16.386 --> 02:18.388
Okay, just for

02:16.386 --> 02:18.388
argument's sake,

02:18.430 --> 02:21.850
let's say Dr. Bombay was

02:18.430 --> 02:21.850
one of the MASH surgeons.

02:21.892 --> 02:23.184
I'd still want

02:21.892 --> 02:23.184
Hawkeye operating

02:23.226 --> 02:25.646
on my perforated aorta.

02:25.687 --> 02:27.648
It's experience

02:25.687 --> 02:27.648
that counts.

02:27.689 --> 02:29.441
Think about it.

02:29.483 --> 02:32.152
(thunder crashing)

02:34.488 --> 02:36.824
Will you hurry up

02:34.488 --> 02:36.824
with those dishes?--

02:34.488 --> 02:36.824
my bubbles are evaporating.

02:36.865 --> 02:38.826
Eric, you're not

02:36.865 --> 02:38.826
going to believe this.

02:38.867 --> 02:42.203
I swear I just saw

02:38.867 --> 02:42.203
Commandant Spangler

02:42.245 --> 02:43.580
standing outside

02:42.245 --> 02:43.580
the window.

02:43.622 --> 02:45.206
That's not even funny,

02:43.622 --> 02:45.206
Francis.

02:45.248 --> 02:47.459
There are some things

02:45.248 --> 02:47.459
you just don't joke about,

02:47.501 --> 02:50.253
and that hook-handed maniac

02:47.501 --> 02:50.253
is at the top of the list.

02:50.295 --> 02:51.212
But he was so real.

02:51.254 --> 02:53.007
It was like being back

02:51.254 --> 02:53.007
at military school.

02:53.048 --> 02:54.341
I know.

02:54.382 --> 02:56.051
For a long time, I saw him

02:54.382 --> 02:56.051
every time I shut my eyes.

02:56.093 --> 02:58.386
You just have to remember

02:56.093 --> 02:58.386
we escaped

02:58.428 --> 02:59.429
from that hellhole.

02:59.471 --> 03:00.514
We made it out

03:00.555 --> 03:02.141
and found better lives

03:00.555 --> 03:02.141
for ourselves.

03:02.181 --> 03:03.142
Now, let's get

03:03.182 --> 03:04.225
these dishes done.

03:04.267 --> 03:05.602
We still have

03:04.267 --> 03:05.602
to snake out the toilets

03:05.644 --> 03:07.104
before we can

03:05.644 --> 03:07.104
call it a night.

03:08.147 --> 03:10.649
(thunder crashing)

03:12.275 --> 03:14.235
Hey, guys, wait up!

03:14.277 --> 03:16.113
(panting)

03:16.905 --> 03:19.198
(clattering)

03:20.450 --> 03:22.243
Hi.

03:22.285 --> 03:24.705
I'm Dewey.

03:24.746 --> 03:26.247
You smell terrible.

03:26.289 --> 03:27.749
I like you.

03:28.876 --> 03:30.961
Maybe you could

03:28.876 --> 03:30.961
come home with me.

03:31.003 --> 03:33.296
Dewey, you're not allowed

03:31.003 --> 03:33.296
to have a dog, remember?

03:33.338 --> 03:35.256
We want you

03:33.338 --> 03:35.256
to be miserable.

03:35.298 --> 03:37.258
That's right, son,

03:35.298 --> 03:37.258
it's our job to make sure

03:37.300 --> 03:39.553
we're as unfair

03:37.300 --> 03:39.553
as possible to you.

03:39.594 --> 03:41.304
Don't listen

03:39.594 --> 03:41.304
to them, Dewey.

03:41.346 --> 03:43.098
I've studied the

03:41.346 --> 03:43.098
matter thoroughly,

03:43.140 --> 03:45.350
and I'm convinced you

03:43.140 --> 03:45.350
can get away with it.

03:45.392 --> 03:49.270
All you have to do

03:45.392 --> 03:49.270
is hide me. Hmm.

03:50.605 --> 03:53.775
I'll call you Marshmallow.

03:55.027 --> 03:57.946
("Tonight's the Night"

03:55.027 --> 03:57.946
playing)

04:01.533 --> 04:05.245
♪ Tonight's the night ♪

04:06.371 --> 04:09.791
♪ It's gonna be all right ♪

04:10.625 --> 04:13.294
♪ 'Cause I love you, girl ♪

04:13.336 --> 04:17.549
♪ Ain't nobody

04:13.336 --> 04:17.549
gonna stop us now... ♪

04:18.967 --> 04:20.301
(laughing)

04:20.343 --> 04:21.553
Hal, what are you doing here?

04:21.595 --> 04:23.304
Well, you're off work

04:21.595 --> 04:23.304
in five minutes,

04:23.346 --> 04:25.724
and I am here to whisk you away

04:23.346 --> 04:25.724
for a night of romance.

04:25.766 --> 04:28.309
Oh, honey, that's so sweet,

04:25.766 --> 04:28.309
but I can't.

04:28.351 --> 04:30.938
I've got to cover

04:28.351 --> 04:30.938
for Craig tonight.

04:30.979 --> 04:32.355
Why?!

04:32.397 --> 04:33.732
Oh, he's sick as a dog.

04:33.774 --> 04:36.317
Come on! You know that guy's

04:33.774 --> 04:36.317
the biggest faker in the world.

04:36.359 --> 04:38.319
The last time

04:36.359 --> 04:38.319
he was out with the flu,

04:38.361 --> 04:42.116
we saw him jumping up and down

04:38.361 --> 04:42.116
in the window on  The Today Show.

04:42.157 --> 04:44.325
That doesn't mean

04:42.157 --> 04:44.325
I wasn't sick.

04:44.367 --> 04:46.327
You didn't happen to tape that,

04:44.367 --> 04:46.327
did you?

04:46.369 --> 04:47.955
I set my timer wrong.

04:47.996 --> 04:49.330
Oh, honey,

04:49.372 --> 04:50.540
I'm so sorry.

04:50.582 --> 04:53.210
After all the trouble

04:50.582 --> 04:53.210
you went through.

04:53.252 --> 04:54.795
No. It's no big deal.

04:54.836 --> 04:57.422
Really, it wasn't any trouble.

04:59.382 --> 05:00.968
Thanks again

04:59.382 --> 05:00.968
for the ride home.

05:01.009 --> 05:02.343
Wow.

05:02.385 --> 05:04.429
So, this is

05:02.385 --> 05:04.429
what it would have been like

05:04.471 --> 05:05.806
to go to my prom.

05:05.847 --> 05:08.349
All I wanted was

05:05.847 --> 05:08.349
a nice evening with my wife.

05:08.391 --> 05:09.350
I even dug up

05:09.392 --> 05:10.644
the wedding vows

05:10.685 --> 05:13.272
I never was able

05:10.685 --> 05:13.272
to read to her.

05:13.354 --> 05:14.355
What happened?

05:14.397 --> 05:16.357
Oh, she went into labor

05:14.397 --> 05:16.357
with Francis

05:16.399 --> 05:17.985
in the middle of the ceremony.

05:18.026 --> 05:21.155
I was going to read

05:18.026 --> 05:21.155
them to her tonight.

05:21.196 --> 05:24.532
God... now I feel awful.

05:24.574 --> 05:26.160
Don't worry

05:24.574 --> 05:26.160
about it, Craig.

05:26.201 --> 05:28.162
It's not your fault.

05:28.203 --> 05:30.371
No, I really feel awful.

05:30.413 --> 05:32.749
(retching)

05:32.791 --> 05:35.794
(Marshmallow whining)

05:42.425 --> 05:44.803
(whining)

05:49.224 --> 05:52.269
Shh.

05:53.228 --> 05:54.604
(whispering):

05:53.228 --> 05:54.604
Are you awake?

05:54.646 --> 05:56.023
(Marshmallow whining)

05:56.064 --> 05:58.566
Oh, honey,

05:56.064 --> 05:58.566
I'm so sorry about tonight.

05:58.608 --> 06:00.652
Listen, tomorrow night,

05:58.608 --> 06:00.652
I'm going to fix us

06:00.694 --> 06:02.403
such a special dinner--

06:00.694 --> 06:02.403
just the two of us.

06:02.445 --> 06:03.613
We'll lock the boys

06:02.445 --> 06:03.613
in the garage,

06:03.655 --> 06:05.406
open a bottle of wine--

06:03.655 --> 06:05.406
it'll be great.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.701
(Marshmallow whining)

06:07.742 --> 06:11.370
Oh, I know, honey, I know.

06:13.748 --> 06:15.458
That's all I have.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.669
(whining)

06:23.050 --> 06:25.177
(sighing)

06:44.403 --> 06:45.530
Is the roast

06:44.403 --> 06:45.530
medium rare?

06:45.572 --> 06:46.907
Did you put the

06:45.572 --> 06:46.907
wine in the fridge?

06:46.948 --> 06:48.533
Mom, my roast

06:46.948 --> 06:48.533
is perfect.

06:48.575 --> 06:50.451
I never even knew

06:48.575 --> 06:50.451
we had fancy silverware.

06:50.493 --> 06:52.453
When was the last time

06:50.493 --> 06:52.453
you used this?

06:52.495 --> 06:53.621
The night you were conceived.

06:53.663 --> 06:54.748
You want more details?

06:54.789 --> 06:55.749
No.

06:54.789 --> 06:55.749
Good.

06:55.790 --> 06:57.709
Thank you so much

06:55.790 --> 06:57.709
for your help!

06:57.751 --> 06:59.753
Now, get in your room,

06:57.751 --> 06:59.753
and don't make a peep

06:59.794 --> 07:00.921
for the next

06:59.794 --> 07:00.921
five hours.

07:00.962 --> 07:02.421
Move!

07:05.008 --> 07:07.468
(Marshmallow whining,

07:05.008 --> 07:07.468
Dewey grunting)

07:07.510 --> 07:08.678
He's not a dog.

07:08.720 --> 07:10.264
He's just pretend.

07:10.305 --> 07:12.140
What's for dinner?

07:10.305 --> 07:12.140
(door closes)

07:12.182 --> 07:14.559
A dog? Busted!

07:14.601 --> 07:16.561
Please don't tell Mom! Please!

07:16.603 --> 07:17.771
Do you have

07:16.603 --> 07:17.771
a death wish?

07:17.812 --> 07:19.314
Just let me have him one night.

07:19.356 --> 07:20.648
I love him, and he loves me.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.649
Please, please!

07:21.691 --> 07:23.484
Okay, Dewey, relax.

07:23.526 --> 07:24.652
We won't tell.

07:24.694 --> 07:27.322
Thank you!

07:27.364 --> 07:28.740
So, when do we tell?

07:28.782 --> 07:30.742
As soon as

07:28.782 --> 07:30.742
Dad gets home.

07:30.784 --> 07:32.119
It'll be funnier.

07:32.160 --> 07:34.079
I couldn't sleep at all

07:32.160 --> 07:34.079
last night.

07:34.121 --> 07:36.415
Me, too. It's like there's

07:34.121 --> 07:36.415
something creepy in the air.

07:36.456 --> 07:37.624
SPANGLER:

07:36.456 --> 07:37.624
Francis!

07:41.169 --> 07:42.503
Commandant Spangler.

07:42.545 --> 07:44.172
(pans clattering)

07:45.257 --> 07:46.716
What are you doing

07:45.257 --> 07:46.716
in Alaska?

07:46.758 --> 07:49.510
I've come for  you,  Francis!

07:49.552 --> 07:53.432
I've been searching for you

07:49.552 --> 07:53.432
for months.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.600
Me? Why?

07:55.642 --> 07:58.145
Why?!

07:58.186 --> 08:01.189
Because...

08:01.231 --> 08:06.320
after 32 years as an educator

08:01.231 --> 08:06.320
and disciplinarian,

08:06.361 --> 08:08.029
your  desertion

08:08.071 --> 08:09.448
stood out as my

08:09.489 --> 08:11.532
only failure--

08:11.574 --> 08:14.035
a  failure  that...

08:14.077 --> 08:17.331
haunted my every waking moment.

08:17.372 --> 08:20.541
I began to see  your face

08:20.583 --> 08:23.544
and those of other

08:20.583 --> 08:23.544
young cadets who didn't

08:23.586 --> 08:26.965
deserve the wrath that I poured

08:23.586 --> 08:26.965
down on their innocent souls.

08:27.007 --> 08:29.217
There was a lawsuit.

08:29.259 --> 08:32.553
Charges were filed.

08:32.595 --> 08:34.389
Disgrace.

08:34.431 --> 08:37.476
I can't even remember the fire.

08:37.517 --> 08:42.147
But I  do  remember the  cause

08:42.189 --> 08:43.564
for all of my

08:43.606 --> 08:45.484
suffering.

08:45.525 --> 08:49.821
I saw the  stupid,  grinning face

08:49.863 --> 08:55.076
of the one person responsible

08:49.863 --> 08:55.076
for all of my suffering.

08:56.119 --> 08:57.371
Who?

08:57.412 --> 08:58.579
(quavering yell):

08:57.412 --> 08:58.579
Die!

08:58.621 --> 09:01.582
Die!

09:01.624 --> 09:03.584
Die!

09:03.626 --> 09:04.836
Die...

09:03.626 --> 09:04.836
Sir, cut it out.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.380
Your hooks are cold.

09:06.421 --> 09:10.550
(drunken sobbing)

09:22.854 --> 09:25.023
And then

09:22.854 --> 09:25.023
Dewey and Marshmallow

09:25.065 --> 09:26.607
killed the evil dragon,

09:26.649 --> 09:28.609
rescued the

09:26.649 --> 09:28.609
poodle princess

09:28.651 --> 09:30.695
and flew all the

09:28.651 --> 09:30.695
way back home.

09:30.737 --> 09:34.615
And they got medals

09:30.737 --> 09:34.615
and big, red capes,

09:34.657 --> 09:36.826
and everybody

09:34.657 --> 09:36.826
loved them.

09:38.119 --> 09:39.620
(whines)

09:39.662 --> 09:41.581
Are you okay?

09:43.666 --> 09:45.126
Marshmallow.

09:45.168 --> 09:47.254
(grunts)

09:45.168 --> 09:47.254
Whoa.

09:47.295 --> 09:48.755
(gasping)

09:50.924 --> 09:52.633
Marshmallow, stop!

09:52.675 --> 09:55.303
LOIS: Boys, I thought I told you

09:52.675 --> 09:55.303
to stay in your room!

09:55.345 --> 09:56.888
Marshmallow, hide!

10:02.519 --> 10:04.729
(growling softly)

10:07.148 --> 10:08.733
I don't understand it!

10:08.775 --> 10:10.527
An entire roast

10:10.569 --> 10:11.945
with your bare hands?!

10:11.986 --> 10:15.656
T-th-the, the

10:11.986 --> 10:15.656
salad, the potatoes,

10:11.986 --> 10:15.656
t-the green beans?!

10:15.698 --> 10:17.951
What do you

10:15.698 --> 10:17.951
have to say for yourself?!

10:17.992 --> 10:19.327
I was hungry, I guess.

10:19.369 --> 10:20.579
This is great.

10:20.620 --> 10:21.662
Let's tell them

10:20.620 --> 10:21.662
about the dog

10:21.704 --> 10:23.331
and really nail

10:21.704 --> 10:23.331
his coffin shut.

10:23.373 --> 10:24.458
Not yet; I

10:23.373 --> 10:24.458
have a hunch.

10:24.499 --> 10:27.377
An entire stick of butter?!

10:27.419 --> 10:28.669
(sotto voce):

10:27.419 --> 10:28.669
Now! Let's tell them now!

10:28.711 --> 10:30.713
Wait for it,

10:28.711 --> 10:30.713
wait for it.

10:30.755 --> 10:32.299
Wait a second.

10:32.340 --> 10:35.510
How could you eat... a candle?

10:35.552 --> 10:36.677
I like candles.

10:36.719 --> 10:38.679
I think they're good.

10:38.721 --> 10:39.889
That's it!

10:39.931 --> 10:43.643
You are going to the hospital

10:39.931 --> 10:43.643
and getting your stomach pumped.

10:48.398 --> 10:49.774
(phone ringing, indistinct

10:48.398 --> 10:49.774
announcement over P.A.)

10:49.816 --> 10:51.692
All right, young man.

10:51.734 --> 10:53.694
I think you're empty.

10:53.736 --> 10:55.363
Well?

10:55.405 --> 10:56.615
He's fine.

10:56.656 --> 10:57.782
We didn't find

10:56.656 --> 10:57.782
any candles,

10:57.824 --> 10:59.326
but we did find

10:57.824 --> 10:59.326
some marbles

10:59.367 --> 11:01.536
and the waistband to

10:59.367 --> 11:01.536
a pair of underpants.

11:01.578 --> 11:02.703
Don't ask.

11:02.745 --> 11:04.914
Thank you, Doctor.

11:04.956 --> 11:07.125
All right, Dewey,

11:04.956 --> 11:07.125
this is the end.

11:07.167 --> 11:08.502
You and your brothers

11:08.543 --> 11:10.711
are now officially

11:08.543 --> 11:10.711
in the red zone.

11:10.753 --> 11:12.380
But...

11:10.753 --> 11:12.380
Red zone, mister!

