19:55.903 --> 20:00.116
the top of the Popsicle stick.

20:00.158 --> 20:01.701
I'm sorry, I have arthritis.

20:01.742 --> 20:02.660
That's it.

20:02.702 --> 20:05.245
You have just lost pudding

20:05.287 --> 20:07.247
for the whole group.

20:07.289 --> 20:12.503
Feel free to thank

20:07.289 --> 20:12.503
Mrs. Meekitjuk after I leave.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.259
I feel like dancing.

20:19.301 --> 20:21.012
Me, too.

20:47.329 --> 20:48.789
Oh, darling,

20:47.329 --> 20:48.789
there's something

20:48.831 --> 20:50.166
I've wanted

20:48.831 --> 20:50.166
to say to you

20:50.208 --> 20:51.291
for the longest time.

20:51.333 --> 20:52.168
Uh-huh?

20:52.210 --> 20:55.922
I have to go

20:52.210 --> 20:55.922
to the hospital.

20:55.963 --> 21:00.593
Oh, Hal, you don't know

20:55.963 --> 21:00.593
how happy that makes me.

21:01.385 --> 21:04.304
REESE:

21:01.385 --> 21:04.304
What do you think?

21:04.346 --> 21:05.347
One more can?

21:05.389 --> 21:07.391
No, we don't want

21:05.389 --> 21:07.391
to spoil him.

21:07.433 --> 21:09.351
Besides,

21:07.433 --> 21:09.351
he probably has to go

21:09.393 --> 21:10.770
to the bathroom now.

21:10.811 --> 21:13.147
Who wants to go out

21:10.811 --> 21:13.147
in the front yard?

21:13.189 --> 21:16.025
I'll remember  this,  too.

21:16.067 --> 21:18.485
"And how can words

21:16.067 --> 21:18.485
describe how I feel

21:18.527 --> 21:20.738
on this, the day

21:18.527 --> 21:20.738
of our marriage?"

21:20.780 --> 21:24.033
"You are my day, my night,

21:20.780 --> 21:24.033
the sun in my sky.

21:24.075 --> 21:26.702
You are the Duran

21:24.075 --> 21:26.702
to my Duran."

21:26.744 --> 21:29.329
Oh, Hal.

21:29.371 --> 21:32.708
"Her name is Lois and

21:29.371 --> 21:32.708
she dances on the sand

21:32.750 --> 21:35.586
just like that river twisting

21:32.750 --> 21:35.586
through a dusty land..."
